The paper deals with video deblurring, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which falls under the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. The study conducted in the paper involves the optimization of model architecture and training procedure, which is related to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also discusses the differences in quantitative and qualitative performance, which is related to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing, which is related to the cs.GR (Graphics) category.
